Film school & Life Coaching in 526 Pages: "Cassavetes on Cassavetes"- I'm celebrating 10 yrs since I bought this by reading it all over again. Most of my books were bought at the old Biography bookstore on Bleecker & West 11th St. (across from Magnolia Bakery) where they'd have shitloads of books for like $5 out in front. I'd go get high, spend like $100 on 4 bags worth of books, go across the street & make fun of the ridiculous assholes waiting 5 hours on line for a cupcake & then walk down W. 11th & watch Julian Schnabel paint in front of his studio/ house windows from the street (before he built that huge palazzo on top). Sometimes i'd run into Lou Reed walking his dog across the street. Other times i'd run into Rene Ricard coming out of Schnabel's & we'd make fun of the cupcake assholes 2gether. 💖 js
